HTML Character Entity References
THESE ARE USED TO HELP DIFFERENTIATE BETWEEN HTML COMMANDS AND TEXT PART OF CONTENT ,   AVAOID RENDERING ISSSUES

&lt; - for '<' 
&gt; - for '>' 
&amp; - for '&' 
&copy; - for use copyright symbol
&nnbsp; - make sure that 3 words in an HTML document ALWAYS appear together on 1 line, even if the text word-wraps because the browser window is too narrow for that text line, so 
        place &nbsp; entity reference after the 1st word and after the 2nd word (with no spaces in between words and entity references)
&quote - for ' " ' double quotes


LINKING PAGES
1) external link 
   <body>
  <h1 id="top">External Links</h1>
  <section>
    <p>
      Let's link to a Facebook Fan page I created for this course!
      <!-- link to Facebook page WITH TARGET-->
      <a href="http://www.facebook.com/CourseraWebDev" 
      target="_blank" title="Like Our Page!">Course Facebook Page</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</body>

2) Internal Links
<body>
  <h1>Internal Links</h1>
  <section>
    We can link to a file in the same directory as this HTML file like this:
    <a href="same-directory.html" title="same dir link">Linking to a file in the same directory</a>

    <a href="same-directory.html" title="same dir link">
      <div> DIV Linking to a file in the same directory</div>
    </a>
  </section>
</body>

3) Same directory
  <title>Same directory as links-internal.html</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Same directory as links-internal.html</h1>
  <a href="links-internal.html" title="Back to internal links page">Back to links-internal.html</a>
</body>

4) Sections of The Same Page
  <h1 id="top">Links to Sections of The Same Page</h1>
  <section>
    <ul>
      <!-- Link to every section in the page -->
      <li><a href="#section1">#section1</a></li>
      <li><a href="#section2">#section2</a></li>
      <li><a href="#section3">#section3</a></li>
      <li><a href="#section4">#section4</a></li>
      <li><a href="#section5">#section5</a></li>
      <li><a href="#section6">#section6</a></li>
    </ul>

  </section>
  
  <section id="section1">
